1
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:12,200
<i>Perfect, I have something
for you to do.</i>

2
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:13,067
<i> What's that, boss?</i>

3
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,900
<i> So, Bobby, let's fix this.</i>

4
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:17,633
<i> Love, Tonyo.</i>

5
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:20,300
<i> Where is he?</i>

6
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:22,533
<i>He's in the office, Ma'am.
At the station, he's busy.</i>

7
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:25,000
<i>We'll talk next time
when he's not busy.</i>

8
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,900
<i> Well, Tonyo is the one coming.</i>

9
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:28,700
<i>He's not the one at fault,
after all.</i>

10
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:30,767
<i> I just want him to apologize.</i>

11
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,733
<i>Well, you know, I'm telling you,
it's hard to be full of pride.</i>

12
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:39,333
<i>That's five million pesos
for Bobby to forgo her claims.</i>

13
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:43,533
<i>If you fight me,
you will get nothing.</i>

14
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:44,600
<i> Well, nothing.</i>

15
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:46,933
<i> Stick it in your lungs!</i>

16
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,600
<i>It was my daughter who committed
a sin against you,</i>

17
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,067
<i> not my granddaughter!</i>

18
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,600
<i> So stop picking on Bobby.</i>

19
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:54,300
<i>You know, Faye, Vince was very
instrumental in stopping</i>

20
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:55,700
<i> the drug trade at your school.</i>

21
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:56,933
<i> What's not to like about him?</i>

22
00:00:57,067 --> 00:00:59,333
<i>But Faye is too young
to have a boyfriend.</i>

23
00:00:59,467 --> 00:01:01,900
<i>Glen, I saw how you looked
at that young man.</i>

24
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:02,900
<i> Don't do it.</i>

25
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:03,967
<i> I won't do anything.</i>

26
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:06,033
<i> Captain didn't cook breakfast.</i>

27
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:07,133
<i> Maybe she's still asleep?</i>

28
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,133
<i> She's not here.</i>

29
00:01:08,267 --> 00:01:09,000
<i> Where's Grandmother?</i>

30
00:01:09,133 --> 00:01:10,100
<i> I'll check outside.</i>

31
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:11,900
<i>- We'll call the village.
- No, I'll do it.</i>

32
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,067
It smells good, ah.

33
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:24,000
Bok, you're early!

34
00:01:25,633 --> 00:01:29,233
I'm early because didn't you say
you'd update me

35
00:01:29,367 --> 00:01:30,900
about the guy
who let Mando escape?

36
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:36,367
But why do you smell so good?

37
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,433
I know.

38
00:01:39,567 --> 00:01:41,533
Because yesterday,

39
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:46,167
I told you that Bobby
would be reporting today.

40
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:49,900
Yes, okay.

41
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:52,567
I came early because I wanted
to talk to her in person.

42
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:54,700
But of course, I'm also
interested in your update.

43
00:01:54,833 --> 00:01:57,233
- What's that?
- Bok, good morning.

44
00:01:59,467 --> 00:02:01,600
Wait, that smells good.
Is that you?

45
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:02,633
It's not me.

46
00:02:02,767 --> 00:02:03,833
It's Bok.

47
00:02:03,967 --> 00:02:07,967
- Because he knows that today...
- Bok, what's with you?

48
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,000
That's enough.

49
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:12,100
Bautista, what are you going
to update us on?

50
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:14,467
Bok, we followed
your suggestion.

51
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:18,100
We went around all the ATMs
near Calabari State Prison.

52
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:20,600
There, Bautista hit the jackpot.

53
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,667
Let me see.
What is that?

54
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:30,433
Sir, the bank's CCTV captured
alias Brando withdrawing.

55
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:33,933
What's this?

56
00:02:36,867 --> 00:02:37,867
Is that it?

57
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:41,767
Bautista.

58
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,000
I'm always with you!

59
00:02:44,133 --> 00:02:46,167
You must be overflowing
with knowledge,

60
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:48,667
and this is all you got?

61
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:50,867
I'm so disappointed in you.

62
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,133
We already know
what that guy looks like.

63
00:02:54,267 --> 00:02:57,033
Bok, look at the one
on the right.

64
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:58,267
There.

65
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:04,567
Sir, the license plate
of the car was also seen

66
00:03:04,700 --> 00:03:05,967
on the CCTV.

67
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:12,000
Bautista, Bautista, Bautista...

68
00:03:12,133 --> 00:03:13,967
I'm so proud of you!

69
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,267
You're really good!

70
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,200
Thank you, Sir.

71
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:18,000
You're really learning
a lot from me.

72
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:19,167
You're really great.

73
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:59,400
Miss, have you seen Grandmother?

74
00:03:59,533 --> 00:04:01,000
Bobby, no.

75
00:04:10,633 --> 00:04:11,600
Bobby!

76
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:13,700
What?

77
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:16,233
We called the village.

78
00:04:16,367 --> 00:04:18,067
They said the Captain
wasn't there.

79
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,633
Where is Grandmother?

80
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:24,033
Bobby, you don't have any
syndicate enemies, right?

81
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:27,100
Because last time, Captain
disappeared, remember?

82
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:29,400
Well, I'm not handling
any cases right now.

83
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,300
Or could it be...

84
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:34,067
- It's possible.
- Wait.

85
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,233
Yes, yes. Mar...

86
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:36,700
What's that?

87
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,800
Abdul, why don't you say it?

88
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:42,967
Well, Bobby, because Captain
was with us last night.

89
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:45,300
Well, the three of us went
out on patrol,

90
00:04:45,433 --> 00:04:48,467
and then we met Ma'am Sophia.

91
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,833
Then...

92
00:04:49,967 --> 00:04:52,500
Yes, Bobby, then Ma'am Sophia
threatened Captain

93
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:54,233
about your inheritance.

94
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:55,433
What?

95
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:04,400
Mom, where were you last night?

96
00:05:04,533 --> 00:05:07,833
When Faye and I went home,
you weren't here.

97
00:05:07,967 --> 00:05:12,267
Well, I tried to talk to Bobby
through her Grandmother,

98
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,367
but she just fought me.

99
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:18,700
Mommy, maybe you were combative
when you went there.

100
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,800
What's wrong with you, Faye?

101
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:28,400
Every time, you take her side
over me, over our family.

102
00:05:28,533 --> 00:05:31,000
Faye, that's enough.

103
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:32,567
If Dad were here,

104
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,767
he wouldn't like you answering
Mom like that.

105
00:05:35,933 --> 00:05:39,600
Glen, if Dad were here,

106
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:42,300
Bobby would be with us
for breakfast.

107
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:44,800
She will be part of this family!

108
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:50,733
How did she threaten her?

109
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:53,900
Okay...

110
00:05:55,233 --> 00:05:59,900
"You're also stubborn,
just like your granddaughter."

111
00:06:00,033 --> 00:06:02,333
That's it. There's more.

112
00:06:02,467 --> 00:06:03,667
That's what she said.

113
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:09,833
"You'll regret that you made
an enemy out of me."

114
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,200
That's it.

115
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:14,500
Bobby, isn't that a threat?

116
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:16,000
That's a threat.

117
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:19,033
So, Bobby, do you think Ma'am
Sophia had anything to do

118
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:20,633
with Captain's disappearance?

119
00:06:20,767 --> 00:06:23,900
Wait, didn't Ma'am Sophia
leave a calling card

120
00:06:24,033 --> 00:06:25,667
in case Captain changes
her mind?

121
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,900
Oh, yes, it's upstairs!

122
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:27,500
Come on.

123
00:06:27,633 --> 00:06:28,267
Let's go, let's go.

124
00:06:32,067 --> 00:06:33,400
You want to play that game?

125
00:06:34,567 --> 00:06:38,500
If Dad were here, he wouldn't
let you date a man,

126
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:40,400
especially a former snatcher.

127
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,500
What?

128
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:45,533
Glen, I thought you liked Vince?

129
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:47,500
Yeah, as a person,

130
00:06:48,567 --> 00:06:51,967
but as a man for you, no.

131
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,933
Faye, that is unacceptable.

132
00:06:57,067 --> 00:07:01,633
Stop seeing that man
your brother is talking about.

133
00:07:01,767 --> 00:07:02,633
Fine!

134
00:07:02,767 --> 00:07:05,167
Okay, gang up on me!

135
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,333
Ever since Daddy died,

136
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:09,467
I've had no allies
in this house!

137
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:13,800
- Faye, come back here!
- Mom, Mom, Mom...

138
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:17,533
Let it go.

139
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:18,700
Maybe you can do something

140
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:21,233
or say something
that we'll regret in the end.

141
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:24,500
I don't know, Glen.

142
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:30,233
Your Daddy's just giving us
more and more problems.

143
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:41,667
How's the contact
I've asked you

144
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,400
to radio in the transportation
department?

145
00:07:43,533 --> 00:07:44,600
Has he replied yet?

146
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:48,500
Sir, Garcia has followed it up.

147
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:50,600
They're just checking the car
records

148
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:51,667
because there's a chance

149
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,600
that the license plate number
used is fake.

150
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:56,967
So I hope this is really
his car.

151
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:09,967
Enriquez's leave is only
for two days.

152
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:12,200
Maybe she's just taking
care of something,

153
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,567
that's why she hasn't reported
to the station yet.

154
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:23,333
Am I being too obvious, Sir?

155
00:08:24,733 --> 00:08:26,133
Yes, Bok!

156
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:28,000
You seem spaced out.

157
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,333
Sorry, Sir.

158
00:08:32,467 --> 00:08:36,033
This is the first time Enriquez
and I will talk in person.

159
00:08:36,167 --> 00:08:38,300
The phone calls aren't working,

160
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:40,433
and we're just getting worse.

161
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:43,300
You know, Conde,

162
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:48,600
I can only suggest one thing
to you when it comes to women...

163
00:08:50,067 --> 00:08:51,033
Well, good luck.

164
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,967
Because there's no expert
when it comes to that.

165
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:56,767
I second the motion.

166
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,467
I got some information.

167
00:09:03,567 --> 00:09:06,467
That's the address and
the person we're looking for.

168
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,667
He's Dante Eusebio.

169
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:12,867
Conde, check the address.

170
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:15,300
Yes, Sir.

171
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:23,300
What the Boss is asking us
to do is boring.

172
00:09:23,433 --> 00:09:26,333
You know, boring is better
than me hanging out

173
00:09:26,467 --> 00:09:27,400
in the safehouse.

174
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:29,367
That's boring.

175
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:34,800
You know, I'm so desperate
to get out of the house,

176
00:09:34,933 --> 00:09:36,633
if you want,
let's swap appearance?

177
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:38,167
But I'm at the losing end.

178
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,233
Hey,

179
00:09:41,267 --> 00:09:44,300
I'm Mr. Campus, 3rd runner-up
during my younger days...

180
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:45,567
3rd runner-up?

181
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:47,033
Why?
How many of you are competing?

182
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:49,200
- Two?
- Crazy!

183
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:53,300
Bad trip.
I still have a date.

184
00:09:53,433 --> 00:09:54,400
You? You have a date?

185
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:57,133
Yes! She's been waiting
at her condo for a while.

186
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:58,433
Did you bring any food?

187
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:04,867
- Faye.
- Vince...

188
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:06,967
We'll go ahead.

189
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,700
- Okay, be careful.
- Okay, be careful.

190
00:10:11,367 --> 00:10:12,933
That's Boss sister.

191
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:17,167
Is that the boyfriend
of Boss's sister?

192
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:19,600
I know him.

193
00:10:30,433 --> 00:10:31,767
<i> I will kill you!</i>

194
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:36,300
That's the reason Monty
went to jail.

195
00:10:38,867 --> 00:10:41,233
The boss said
he was a police asset.

196
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,700
What's your problem?

197
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:49,833
Why are you looking like that?

198
00:10:49,967 --> 00:10:51,567
No, nothing, I'm fine.

199
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:56,967
As soon as you got here,
I knew you had a problem.

200
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:59,967
No, nothing, Vince.
It's really fine.

201
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:04,067
Before, when I didn't tell you
something, you'd get angry.

202
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,967
Then now, you're the one
who doesn't want to talk.

203
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:11,067
Because Mommy and I had a fight.

204
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,533
With Glen too,
earlier at breakfast.

205
00:11:13,667 --> 00:11:15,633
Oh, why?
What's your fault?

206
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:17,867
Maybe you're stubborn, right?

207
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:22,667
Vince, because...

208
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:27,233
they don't want me going out
with you.

209
00:11:27,367 --> 00:11:30,100
You know, I understand
your Mommy and Glen.

210
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:33,133
They just want
to make you better.

211
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:37,000
So don't fight them anymore.

212
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:40,400
Vince, this is my life.

213
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:43,900
They can't force me to do
something that I don't like.

214
00:11:44,067 --> 00:11:45,800
You know,

215
00:11:45,933 --> 00:11:47,767
fishball and kikiam
will do wonders.

216
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,867
I'll treat you later.

217
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,367
What, is your class over?

218
00:11:53,967 --> 00:11:55,533
I have another class.

219
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:59,033
Okay, text me when it's over.

220
00:11:59,167 --> 00:12:00,867
I'll just come back here.

221
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,300
- Okay, Vince, text me, okay?
- Okay.

222
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,500
Let's bury that in the ground.

223
00:12:06,633 --> 00:12:08,267
Oh, wait, wait.
Where are you going?

224
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,100
Bury it in the ground,
Boss said.

225
00:12:10,233 --> 00:12:12,433
What are you doing?
You're too hot.

226
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:14,067
I have people for this.

227
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,400
Go on your date.

228
00:12:15,567 --> 00:12:16,333
I'll take care of it.

229
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:18,433
- Are you sure?
- I'm sure.

230
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:20,367
This is our deal,

231
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:21,667
when you get back to the
hideout,

232
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,467
bring me a kartada-sais, okay.

233
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:25,900
Okay.

234
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:27,700
I can do this.

235
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:28,833
You can go.

236
00:12:44,667 --> 00:12:45,667
Hello.

237
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,333
It's your chance
to have a job.

238
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,767
I have something
for you to do.

239
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:03,500
Hello?

240
00:13:03,633 --> 00:13:05,133
Hello, Ma'am Sophia?

241
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:08,033
This is Sergeant Bobby Enriquez.

242
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:12,133
So, how may I be of service
to our police force,

243
00:13:12,267 --> 00:13:13,533
Sergeant Enriquez?

244
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:19,567
Someone told me that you spoke
to Grandmother last night.

245
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:24,500
Yes, I tried to talk to her,
but she wouldn't listen.

246
00:13:24,633 --> 00:13:25,900
She's missing.

247
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:27,800
We've been looking for her
for some time now.

248
00:13:27,933 --> 00:13:30,800
We're calling her,
but we couldn't get in touch.

249
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:31,833
So?

250
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:34,700
Between the two of us,
you're the police,

251
00:13:34,833 --> 00:13:36,867
so why are you telling me this?

252
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:40,433
Wait...

253
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,367
Are you trying to insinuate
that I had something to do

254
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:45,967
with your grandmother's
disappearance?

255
00:13:47,367 --> 00:13:50,267
I have witnesses who say
that you threatened

256
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:51,600
my grandmother last night.

257
00:13:51,733 --> 00:13:55,500
Yes, but if I remember
my words correctly,

258
00:13:55,667 --> 00:13:56,767
what I told her,

259
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:59,800
she will regret making
an enemy out of me.

260
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:03,500
I'll make sure
you don't get anything

261
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:05,800
from what Joaquin
bequeathed you.

262
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:07,867
But that's it, Bobby.

263
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,967
I am not a criminal,
much less a kidnapper!

264
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:33,767
Mister, help.

265
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:34,867
Okay, Mother.

266
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:41,100
- What? Mother, be careful.
- Oh, thank you.

267
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,300
Where am I?

268
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,133
What place is this?

269
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:14,633
I'm sorry, Ma'am Sophia.

270
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:17,833
Well, we checked everywhere
but she's nowhere to be found.

271
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:21,767
Grandmother is getting old.

272
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,900
Sometimes, she's having
a hard time walking.

273
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:28,200
If it's going
to take even longer,

274
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:30,267
maybe something
will happen to her.

275
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:31,600
You know, Bobby,

276
00:15:31,733 --> 00:15:35,233
I had nothing to do with your
Grandmother's disappearance,

277
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:39,367
even if I die,
or my family dies.

278
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,767
Okay, I'm sorry.

279
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:44,633
What did she say, Bobby?

280
00:15:46,267 --> 00:15:47,533
She said she didn't know.

281
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:04,467
Wait, I'll just call Noble.

282
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:08,800
Hello, Noble?

283
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:10,933
I need your help.

284
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:12,600
Grandmother is missing.

285
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:13,833
I'll ask for your help.

286
00:16:13,967 --> 00:16:15,367
Where are you, Captain?

287
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:18,033
Maybe something might happen
to Captain.

288
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,900
Where am I?

289
00:16:22,033 --> 00:16:23,467
What place is this?

290
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:26,367
Miss...

291
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,600
What is that, Mother?

292
00:16:27,733 --> 00:16:28,767
I have a question.

293
00:16:29,933 --> 00:16:31,233
What place is this?

294
00:16:31,367 --> 00:16:32,700
Sta. Teresa.

295
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:36,967
Sta. Teresa, it's far
from our place.

296
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:39,700
Are you lost?
Where are you from?

297
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,567
I don't remember.

298
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:46,167
That's okay, Mother.
I'll help you.

299
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:47,867
What's your name?

300
00:16:51,667 --> 00:16:53,000
I don't remember.

301
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:55,433
You don't remember your name?

302
00:16:57,667 --> 00:16:59,800
Do you have a cell phone?

303
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:00,867
Cell phone?

304
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:02,900
None.

305
00:17:03,033 --> 00:17:07,167
ID or wallet, so we can know
where you're from.

306
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:08,167
Wallet?

307
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,267
Yes.

308
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:16,467
There.

309
00:17:18,633 --> 00:17:20,200
Hey, hey, give that back!

310
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:24,467
- My wallet!
- Get it, quick! Snatcher!

311
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:27,933
Where's my wallet?

312
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:31,800
Bobby still hasn't reported,
Bautista said.

313
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:36,033
She's probably still enjoying
her vacation.

314
00:17:36,167 --> 00:17:37,433
She's making the most of it.

315
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,500
I know you're thinking
about her,

316
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:43,067
that's why I told you.

317
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:47,933
Wait a minute.

318
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,933
What are we doing here?

319
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:52,033
I asked my informant.

320
00:17:52,167 --> 00:17:54,300
He said the target
often comes here.

321
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:56,100
It seems like he is visiting
someone in that building.

322
00:17:57,367 --> 00:18:00,000
Wow, he has a love life.

323
00:18:00,133 --> 00:18:00,900
What's up, Bok?

324
00:18:01,033 --> 00:18:03,567
What's our style of attack
this time?

325
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:04,633
When he gets out,

326
00:18:04,767 --> 00:18:06,333
are we going to attack him
right away?

327
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,933
Or do you have a good idea?

328
00:18:10,067 --> 00:18:12,700
Do you want me to get off?

329
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:14,433
Just wait here in the car.

330
00:18:14,567 --> 00:18:16,200
I'll attack him.

331
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:19,100
Then if we get into a fight,

332
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:21,733
I'm sure he won't be the one
to hold me back.

333
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,100
Let's just observe him for now.

334
00:18:24,233 --> 00:18:26,000
Follow him if we can.

335
00:18:26,133 --> 00:18:29,767
But the important thing is,
we'll find out who his boss is.

336
00:18:31,133 --> 00:18:35,300
You're right. Actually,
that's what it is, my idea.

337
00:18:35,433 --> 00:18:37,700
We're really
on the same wavelength.

338
00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:43,133
Who's that?
Is it Bobby?

339
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:47,500
No, it's Corporal Matibag.

340
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:50,433
Asking when his
and Vince's next assignment is.

341
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:58,467
Hello, babe?

342
00:19:00,533 --> 00:19:02,600
I'm outside.

343
00:19:02,733 --> 00:19:03,733
I'm busy.

344
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:05,800
You know I'm a busy person,
right?

345
00:19:05,933 --> 00:19:07,500
Sir Tonyo texted me.

346
00:19:07,633 --> 00:19:09,200
He said we're just on standby
for now.

347
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:11,767
We've been hanging out
for a while.

348
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:14,467
Well, I hope he gives us
an assignment.

349
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,900
Don't you want that?

350
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:18,600
Bro, it's so nice to hang out.

351
00:19:18,733 --> 00:19:20,100
- Hang out.
- Wait.

352
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:21,800
Why are you so hot-headed?

353
00:19:23,767 --> 00:19:25,167
Bro, I already know this.

354
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:26,667
You and Faye fought, didn't you?

355
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:27,867
No, Bro.

356
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,400
We didn't fight.

357
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:33,700
She fought
with her mommy and brother.

358
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:34,833
Why?

359
00:19:34,967 --> 00:19:39,233
Bro, they don't like me.

360
00:19:39,367 --> 00:19:41,433
That's a problem, Bro.

361
00:19:41,567 --> 00:19:43,400
So what's the reason
they don't like you?

362
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:45,000
Bro, what else?

363
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:47,300
Of course, my background.

364
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:50,033
A former snatcher, a bum,

365
00:19:51,467 --> 00:19:52,967
because I haven't graduated yet.

366
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:55,067
I know what to do.

367
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:56,800
I have a solution for that.

368
00:19:56,933 --> 00:19:58,333
Dude, keep going.

369
00:19:58,467 --> 00:19:59,867
Why don't you pursue your dream
of becoming a police officer?

370
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,033
Bro, I haven't graduated.

371
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,567
How can I be a police officer?

372
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:05,967
I know, Bro,

373
00:20:06,100 --> 00:20:08,833
there's an exam for that
so you can get a diploma

374
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:10,767
even if you didn't finish
your studies,

375
00:20:10,900 --> 00:20:13,633
or we can ask Sir Tonyo
for help...

376
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:18,167
if you're really serious
about changing for Faye.

377
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:19,733
Sure, Bro.

378
00:20:21,433 --> 00:20:23,367
Okay, Bro, I'll ask around.

379
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,467
I don't want to be
a bum anymore.

380
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,467
Okay, Bro.

381
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,900
Promise, Bro, I'll do better.

382
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:31,633
Maybe I'll be even higher
in rank than you.

383
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:33,067
Jerk!

384
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:36,333
Okay, let me call my friend
and ask about the requirements.

385
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:37,733
Okay, Bro.

386
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:38,933
Just stay there, okay?

387
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,000
PO1 Vince De Leon.

388
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,100
Okay, that sounds good.

389
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:46,967
Sorry, I bothered you.

390
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:49,233
I really don't know
what to do anymore.

391
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:51,000
Don't worry,
Sergeant Enriquez.

392
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:53,100
We'll help you find
your grandmother.

393
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:54,433
What, Bobby?

394
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:56,200
Is your grandmother missing?

395
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,300
You're a neglectful
granddaughter.

396
00:20:58,433 --> 00:21:00,100
Charlie!

397
00:21:00,233 --> 00:21:02,633
What Lieutenant Samson said
was right.

398
00:21:02,767 --> 00:21:05,433
It's also my fault
that it happened.

399
00:21:05,567 --> 00:21:08,067
I noticed that something strange
was happening to Grandmother.

400
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,667
But I didn't do anything
about it.

401
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:16,800
Lieutenant Paloma, would
it be okay if you include

402
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:18,433
the search for Grandmother
in your patrol?

403
00:21:18,567 --> 00:21:22,000
We really don't know where
to look for her anymore.

404
00:21:22,133 --> 00:21:24,533
Okay, Bobby, we'll help.

405
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:25,867
Thank you.

406
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:31,767
Lieutenant Conde
and Lieutenant Garcia

407
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,400
are already in the field.

408
00:21:33,533 --> 00:21:36,000
Do you want us to tell them
about your grandmother?

409
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:37,800
Don't bother them anymore.

410
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:39,800
They're watching Dante Eusebio,

411
00:21:39,933 --> 00:21:43,167
and there's a lot of us here
at Station 12 that can help.

412
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:44,200
Yes, that's right.

413
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:45,800
Right, don't bother
them anymore.

414
00:21:57,133 --> 00:21:59,033
Okay, hang up the phone.

415
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:04,200
You, you first.
Come on, you first.

416
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:06,167
Okay, okay,
let's do it together.

417
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:07,467
I'll count...

418
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:10,467
One, two, three.

419
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:14,333
You haven't hung up yet!

420
00:22:14,467 --> 00:22:16,600
You said you'd hang up.

421
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:21,667
Okay, okay.
Tonyo is angry.

422
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,167
He looks angry.

423
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:25,967
Who are you talking to?

424
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:29,033
Nothing, it's just
my imagination.

425
00:22:29,167 --> 00:22:32,100
You know, just in case.

426
00:22:32,233 --> 00:22:33,367
Stop that.

427
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,033
Later, Dante might escape
from us.

428
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:38,867
Okay, bye.

429
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:42,067
Just practice.

430
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:45,500
It's really hard to have
a love life, isn't it?

431
00:22:45,633 --> 00:22:47,567
Look at this Dante,

432
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,933
he'll get into danger because
of his love life.

433
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:52,600
Seriously, love life
will really ruin you.

434
00:22:56,667 --> 00:22:57,967
There's the car.

435
00:23:02,933 --> 00:23:03,667
That's it.

436
00:23:08,633 --> 00:23:09,800
That's Dante.

437
00:23:26,167 --> 00:23:27,733
- Hello?
- Hello, Dante?

438
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:29,667
Did you know that
they already know you

439
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:30,967
here at Station 12?

440
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:32,100
How?

441
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:35,667
They already know your full name
and where you live.

442
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:36,733
And at this hour,

443
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:39,000
there are probably police
officers watching you.

444
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,067
What should I do?

445
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,467
Just relax for now.

446
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,633
How can I relax?

447
00:23:44,767 --> 00:23:46,333
I'm still trying to figure out
what their plan is.

448
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:48,800
What if your fellow police
officers kill me?

449
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,900
Where are they stationed?

450
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,567
Right now, I don't know.

451
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,967
But keep an eye
on your surroundings.

452
00:23:56,467 --> 00:24:00,567
<i>You might see a car
with N-A-Q 2-9-1-8.</i>

453
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:04,067
Why doesn't it seem like
he's still not getting out?

454
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:05,600
He'll get out, too.

455
00:24:06,833 --> 00:24:08,533
Just be alert.

456
00:24:08,667 --> 00:24:12,900
Bok, he's talking to someone
on the phone.

457
00:24:16,233 --> 00:24:17,633
They are here.

458
00:24:19,033 --> 00:24:19,967
What are you going to do?

459
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:21,400
I'll get ahead of them.

460
00:24:21,533 --> 00:24:22,500
What's with you?

461
00:24:22,633 --> 00:24:24,400
The best thing you can do
is get out of there.

462
00:24:24,533 --> 00:24:28,367
Because if they catch you
and put the boss in danger,

463
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:29,867
your family will definitely
be hurt.

464
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:32,067
I won't let them catch you.

465
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,233
Dante...

466
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:35,833
Dante!

467
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:01,500
Bok...

468
00:25:01,633 --> 00:25:02,767
He's coming down, Bok.

469
00:25:11,033 --> 00:25:12,967
Bok, why does he seem
to be getting closer to us?

470
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,033
It looks like he's been warned.

471
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:18,567
Bok, get down!

472
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:47,467
Tokboy!

473
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,500
Gotcha!

474
00:25:48,633 --> 00:25:49,667
Look at this.

475
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:50,933
This is Captain Isang's.

476
00:25:51,067 --> 00:25:51,567
Why do you have this?

477
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:52,933
You know my job, right?

478
00:25:53,067 --> 00:25:54,133
You're still thinking
about something.

479
00:25:54,267 --> 00:25:56,167
- Are you Vince?
- Why? What do you need?

480
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,533
What did I do wrong?

481
00:25:57,667 --> 00:25:58,933
Stay away from Faye Guerrero.

482
00:25:59,067 --> 00:26:00,300
I just talked to your sister.

483
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:00,933
And?

484
00:26:01,067 --> 00:26:02,833
Someone beat Vince up.

485
00:26:02,967 --> 00:26:04,300
It was you, right?

486
00:26:04,433 --> 00:26:05,933
Put down your gun.

487
00:26:06,067 --> 00:26:07,200
Sir, I'm not going to fight
back!

488
00:26:07,333 --> 00:26:08,900
Dante, put down your gun!

489
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:11,967
Bobby, let's go home.
I'm not sick.

490
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:13,367
How's Grandmother?

491
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:15,033
It's possible
that she has dementia.

492
00:26:15,167 --> 00:26:16,467
Dementia?
